			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First thing I want to touch on would be a radical change to the way the fire pet works.  For starters, give the pet very high resists similar to Servant of Ro.  Also, give it very low hit points, something like say 250.  Its melee damage should be dropped to perhaps a max hit of 10, with a very long melee delay, like say 60.  Give it an innately-cast DD spell that checks at -100 but Chromatic resist check.  The pet should cast this spell every 3 seconds, while its spell damage should be pretty much in line with hasted Earth pet melee.  This special DD can be scaled up with pet foci.
<br />

<br />
(Advantages, consistent raid dps. Pretty easy to maneuver into position.  Very limited push.  High AoE survivability.   Disadvantages, absolutely cannot tank.  Pet would not be top dps pet in xp groups.  With limited hps cannot be considered a great pvp either.)
<br />

<br />
Second, allow the Rage of Zomm pet to coexist with a primary pet.
<br />

<br />
Third, add an AA, 72 minute refresh, 1 sec cast that allows your current pet to leave a corpse when it dies, in order to recover any weapons or equipment given to the pet.
<br />

<br />
Fourth, change all of our item summons to be targetable, much like Rods.
<br />

<br />
Fifth, alter the refresh on Frenzied Burnout to 3 minutes.
<br />

<br />
Sixth, add a Divine Aura-type spell or AA for pet-only, similar refresh and duration to the cleric spell.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
